<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-31T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="2" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/12–3147: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-31T18:00:00-05:00">December
                                    31, 1947—6 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1594. Nov 30 issue <hi rend="italic">Monthly Report</hi> published by
                            Millard Publishing Co carries story ChiGovt after capture Chefoo found
                            large supplies US arms ammo reportedly obtained by Communists from
                            National Govt sources through arms ring. Emb requested report any info
                            obtainable this story.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>